CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 14, 1941, pg. 11, reads: "There is something new under the sun, at least, Eleather Clements in her Broad Street Shop has found it. She gave a manicure party for her patrons last Wednesday which was novel and successful... Below: Mary Tracy giving Alberta Turner an arch while Gladys Coles gives her a shapely manicure... - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Alberta Tuner having manicure by Gladys Coles, and her eyebrows plucked by Mary Tracy, in Clement's Beauty Salon, East Liberty
